#
# Fixes Claude API tool_use/tool_result adjacency for agent clients that
# round-trip OpenAI Chat Completions and Responses tool turns through CLIProxy.
#
# Root cause: the prior patch merged only consecutive parallel tool results.
# OpenAI Responses can also split one logical turn across adjacent `message`,
# `function_call`, and `function_call_output` items. Reconstructing those as
# separate Claude messages can leave tool_result blocks outside the immediate
# next user message after tool_use.
#
# Changes:
#   - Chat Completions translator keeps parallel tool_result blocks merged
#   - Responses translator merges assistant text + function_call items into one
#     assistant Claude message and keeps tool_result blocks at the front of the
#     first user message even when user text is also present
#   - Adds request-side regression tests for mixed Responses turns
#
